Name: Berber
Description: 1009 – Berber forces led by Sulayman ibn al-Hakam defeat the Umayyad caliph Muhammad II of Córdoba in the Battle of Qantish.

Name: Lý Anh Tông
Description: 1138 – Lý Anh Tông is enthroned as emperor of Vietnam at the age of two, beginning a 37-year reign.

Name: Catholicon
Description: 1499 – The Catholicon, written in 1464 by Jehan Lagadeuc in Tréguier, is published; this is the first Breton dictionary as well as the first French dictionary.

Name: Second Battle of Panipat
Description: 1556 – Second Battle of Panipat: Fighting begins between the forces of Hem Chandra Vikramaditya, the Hindu king at Delhi and the forces of the Muslim emperor Akbar.

Name: Gunpowder Plot
Description: 1605 – Gunpowder Plot: Guy Fawkes is arrested in the cellars of the Houses of Parliament, where he had planted gunpowder in an attempt to blow up the building and kill King James I of England.

Name: Prince William III of Orange
Description: 1688 – Prince William III of Orange lands with a Dutch fleet at Brixham to challenge the rule of King James II of England (James VII of Scotland).

Name: Seven Years' War
Description: 1757 – Seven Years' War: Frederick the Great defeats the allied armies of France and the Holy Roman Empire at the Battle of Rossbach.

Name: Treaty of Fort Stanwix
Description: 1768 – The Treaty of Fort Stanwix is signed, the purpose of which is to adjust the boundary line between Indian lands and white settlements set forth in the Royal Proclamation of 1763 in the Thirteen Colonies.

Name: Colonel LaBalme
Description: 1780 – French-American forces under Colonel LaBalme are defeated by Miami Chief Little Turtle.

Name: José Matías Delgado
Description: 1811 – Salvadoran priest José Matías Delgado rings the bells of La Merced church in San Salvador, calling for insurrection and launching the 1811 Independence Movement.

Name: Greek War of Independence
Description: 1828 – Greek War of Independence: The French Morea expedition to recapture Morea (now the Peloponnese) ends when the last Ottoman forces depart the peninsula.

Name: Free University of Brussels
Description: 1834 – Founding of the Free University of Brussels by Pierre-Théodore Verhaegen.

Name: American Civil War
Description: 1862 – American Civil War: Abraham Lincoln removes George B. McClellan as commander of the Army of the Potomac.

Name: American Indian Wars
Description: 1862   – American Indian Wars: In Minnesota, 303 Dakota warriors are found guilty of rape and murder of whites and are sentenced to death. Thirty-eight are ultimately hanged and the others reprieved.

Name: Women's suffrage in the United States
Description: 1872 – Women's suffrage in the United States: In defiance of the law, suffragist Susan B. Anthony votes for the first time, and is later fined $100.

Name: New Zealand
Description: 1881 – In New Zealand, 1600 armed volunteers and constabulary field forces led by Minister of Native Affairs John Bryce march on the pacifist Māori settlement at Parihaka, evicting upwards of 2000 residents, and destroying the settlement in the context of the New Zealand land confiscations.

Name: George B. Selden
Description: 1895 – George B. Selden is granted the first U.S. patent for an automobile.

Name: Negrese
Description: 1898 – Negrese nationalists revolt against Spanish rule and establish the short-lived Republic of Negros.

Name: Ottoman Empire
Description: 1911 – After declaring war on the Ottoman Empire on September 29, 1911, Italy annexes Tripoli and Cyrenaica.

Name: Woodrow Wilson
Description: 1912 – Woodrow Wilson is elected the 28th President of the United States, defeating incumbent William Howard Taft.

Name: Otto of Bavaria
Description: 1913 – King Otto of Bavaria is deposed by his cousin, Prince Regent Ludwig, who assumes the title Ludwig III.

Name: World War I
Description: 1914 – World War I: France and the British Empire declare war on the Ottoman Empire.

Name: Kingdom of Poland
Description: 1916 – The Kingdom of Poland is proclaimed by the Act of 5th November of the emperors of Germany and Austria-Hungary.

Name: Everett massacre
Description: 1916   – The Everett massacre takes place in Everett, Washington as political differences lead to a shoot-out between the Industrial Workers of the World organizers and local police.

Name: October Revolution
Description: 1917 – Lenin calls for the October Revolution.

Name: Tikhon
Description: 1917   – Tikhon is elected the Patriarch of Moscow and of the Russian Orthodox Church.

Name: Secret agent
Description: 1925 – Secret agent Sidney Reilly, the first "super-spy" of the 20th century, is executed by the OGPU, the secret police of the Soviet Union.

Name: World War II
Description: 1940 – World War II: The British armed merchant cruiser HMS Jervis Bay is sunk by the German pocket battleship Admiral Scheer.

Name: Franklin D. Roosevelt
Description: 1940   – Franklin D. Roosevelt is the first and only President of the United States to be elected to a third term.

Name: Bombing of the Vatican
Description: 1943 – World War II: Bombing of the Vatican.

Name: anti-Jewish riots in Tripolitania
Description: 1945 – The three-day anti-Jewish riots in Tripolitania commence.

Name: Korean War
Description: 1950 – Korean War: British and Australian forces from the 27th British Commonwealth Brigade successfully halted the advancing Chinese 117th Division during the Battle of Pakchon.

Name: Vienna State Opera
Description: 1955 – After being destroyed in World War II, the rebuilt Vienna State Opera reopens with a performance of Beethoven's Fidelio.

Name: Suez Crisis
Description: 1956 – Suez Crisis: British and French paratroopers land in Egypt after a week-long bombing campaign.

Name: Richard Nixon
Description: 1968 – Richard Nixon is elected as 37th President of the United States.

Name: Military Assistance Command, Vietnam
Description: 1970 – The Military Assistance Command, Vietnam reports the lowest weekly American soldier death toll in five years (24).

Name: Byford Dolphin
Description: 1983 – The Byford Dolphin diving bell accident kills five and leaves one severely injured.

Name: USS Rentz
Description: 1986 – USS Rentz, USS Reeves and USS Oldendorf visit Qingdao, China; the first US naval visit to China since 1949.

Name: Meir Kahane
Description: 1990 – Rabbi Meir Kahane, founder of the far-right Kach movement, is shot dead after a speech at a New York City hotel.

Name: Tropical Storm Thelma
Description: 1991 – Tropical Storm Thelma causes flash floods in the Philippine city of Ormoc, killing more than 4,900 people.

Name: André Dallaire
Description: 1995 – André Dallaire attempts to assassinate Prime Minister Jean Chrétien of Canada. He is thwarted when the Prime Minister's wife locks the door.

Name: Pakistani President
Description: 1996 – Pakistani President Farooq Leghari dismisses the government of Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto and dissolves the National Assembly.

Name: Bill Clinton
Description: 1996   – Bill Clinton is reelected President of the United States.

Name: Saddam Hussein
Description: 2006 – Saddam Hussein, the former president of Iraq, and his co-defendants Barzan Ibrahim al-Tikriti and Awad Hamed al-Bandar, are sentenced to death in the al-Dujail trial for their roles in the 1982 massacre of 148 Shia Muslims.

Name: Chang'e 1
Description: 2007 – China's first lunar satellite, Chang'e 1, goes into orbit around the Moon.

Name: Android
Description: 2007   – The Android mobile operating system is unveiled by Google.

Name: Nidal Hasan
Description: 2009 – U.S. Army Major Nidal Hasan murders 13 and wounds 32 at Fort Hood, Texas in the deadliest mass shooting at a U.S. military installation.

Name: JS Air Flight 201
Description: 2010 – JS Air Flight 201 crashes after takeoff from Jinnah International Airport in Karachi, Pakistan, killing all 21 aboard.

Name: Mars Orbiter Mission
Description: 2013 – India launches the Mars Orbiter Mission, its first interplanetary probe.

Name: iron ore
Description: 2015 – An iron ore tailings dam bursts in the Brazilian state of Minas Gerais, flooding a valley, causing mudslides in the nearby village of Bento Rodrigues and causing at least 17 deaths and two missing.

Name: Rona Ambrose
Description: 2015   – Rona Ambrose takes over after Stephen Harper as the Leader of the Conservative Party of Canada.

Name: kills 26 and injures 22
Description: 2017 – Devin Patrick Kelley kills 26 and injures 22 in a church in Sutherland Springs, Texas.

Name: Astroworld Festival crowd crush
Description: 2021 – The Astroworld Festival crowd crush results in 10 deaths and 25 people being hospitalized

Name: Donald Trump
Description: 2024 – Donald Trump becomes the first president of the United States to be elected to a non-consecutive second term in 132 years, since Grover Cleveland won the 1892 election.
